└── storage/                    # File storage
2.3 Database Models & Relationships
Model	Key Attributes	Relationships
User	name, email, level, total_xp, timezone, avatar_url, goal, preferred_duration	hasMany UserWorkouts, hasMany Metrics, hasOne Streak, belongsToMany Achievements, hasMany Reminders
Workout	name, description, duration, difficulty	hasMany WorkoutMoves, hasMany UserWorkouts
WorkoutMove	name, sets, reps, weight, description	belongsTo Workout
UserWorkout	completed_at, workout_duration, calories_burned	belongsTo User, belongsTo Workout
Streak	current_streak, longest_streak, last_workout_date	belongsTo User
Metric	name, value, recorded_at	belongsTo User
Achievement	name, description, icon_url, requirement	belongsToMany Users
Reminder	reminder_time, message, is_active	belongsTo User
Notification	title, message, read_at	belongsTo User
2.4 Key Controllers
DashboardController: Main dashboard and metrics overview
WorkoutController: Workout management and completion
StreakController: Streak tracking and history
AchievementController: Achievement display and management
ProgressController: Progress metrics and visualization
CalendarController: Calendar view of workouts
OnboardingController: Multi-step user onboarding
SettingsController: User preferences
ProfileController: User profile management
AchievementController: Achievement tracking
3. Development & Deployment
3.1 Development Environment
# Setup commands (from composer.json)
composer install
npm install
npm run build
php artisan key:generate
php artisan migrate

# Development server
npm run dev          # Vite development server
php artisan serve    # Laravel development server
php artisan queue:listen    # Queue listener
3.2 Build & Production
Frontend Build:

Vite bundler for optimized JavaScript/CSS
Tailwind CSS with PostCSS processing
Static asset management
Backend Build:

Laravel Sail containerization support
Deployment to Vercel (configured in vercel.json)
Queue job processing support
3.3 Deployment Configuration
Vercel Deployment:

PHP runtime via @vercel/php builder
Static asset handling for CSS/JS
Routing configuration for SPA compatibility
Database integration with production database (Postgres/MySQL)
3.4 Testing
# Test execution
composer test     # Run PHPUnit tests
Dependencies include PHPUnit 11.5.50, Mockery, and Laravel testing utilities.

4. User Features & Workflows
4.1 Authentication & Onboarding
Route: / (welcome)
Process:

User registers/logs in (Laravel Breeze authentication)
Multi-step onboarding (Step 1, 2, 3)
Middleware enforcement (EnsureOnboardingIsCompleted)
Access to main application after completion
4.2 Core User Workflows
Workout Management
View all available workouts
Complete workouts and log duration
Track individual exercises within workouts
Dashboard & Metrics
Overview of current streak
Recent activity summary
